# Redirects served by Cloudflare Workers static assets (this file, public/_redirects).
# Format: /old-url  /new-url  301
#
# IMPORTANT — the site uses trailingSlash: 'always'. ALWAYS point the target at
# the trailing-slash form (/new-url/, NOT /new-url). Otherwise every hit takes
# two hops — your 301, then an automatic 308 that adds the slash — which wastes
# a little SEO equity and adds latency. Point straight at /new-url/.
#
# Use 301 for permanent redirects (renamed pages/posts — passes SEO equity).
# Use 302 for temporary redirects.
#
# NOTE — this file ships in the TEMPLATE, so it is shared by EVERY client site.
# Only put redirects here that are correct for all clients, and whose target
# page exists on all of them (a redirect to a 404 is worse than no redirect).
# Client-specific old->new mappings (e.g. a Squarespace migration) belong on
# that client's own domain via Cloudflare Bulk Redirects, NOT here.
#
# Examples:
#   /about-us          /about/          301
#   /blog/old-title    /blog/new-title/ 301
#
# Add your redirects below this line:

# Common alias paths users may type. Targets are trailing-slash (single hop)
# and point at pages that exist on every client.
/home       /            301
/inquire    /contact/    301
/work       /portfolio/  301
